<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-27T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-27T18:00:00-05:00" n="1122" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1122">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/1470: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Long</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-27T19:00:00-04:00">June 27,
                                    1944—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>367. The Department assumes that the “good offices” referred to in your
                            telegram no. 402, June 25, 12 noon, relate exclusively to the
                            transmission of messages between the contending factions and do not
                            involve the preparation and submission of formulas of settlement, et
                            cetera.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Mexico and other missions in Central America.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>